 theinterfaces between them. Texts and authors discussed include Ian McEwan's Saturday; Sheridan le Fanu; The Birth of Mankind; Franco Morretti; Anna Barbauld; Dorothy L. Sayers; The Cloud of Unknowing; George Eliot and Mary Wollstonecraft. Dr SHARON RUSTON is Senior Lecturer in English at the University of Keele. CONTRIBUTORS: SHARON RUSTON, GILLIAN RUDD, ELAINE HOBBY, ALICE JENKINS, KATY PRICE, MARTIN WILLIS, BRIAN BAKER, DAVID AMIGONI  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aEnglish literaturexHistory and criticism. 0aLiterature and sciencexHistory. 0aScience in literature. 4aEnglish & American Literature. 4aHistory of Science & Medicine. 4aMedieval Literature. 4aModern Literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / American / General.2bisacsh  aC. P. Snow.  aLiterature and science.  acomplex relationship.  aliterary intellectuals.  aliterary parody.  aliterary theory.  aliterature and science.  aliterature.  ascience.  ascientific innovation.  atwo cultures.1 aAmigoni, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBaker, Brian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHobby, Elaine, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJenkins, Alice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPrice, Katy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRudd, Gillian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuston, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRuston, Sharon, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWillis, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBoydell and Brewer Complete eBook-Package pre 2013z978311143139